<SiteLayout title="Privacy Policy | SyntheticBrew" description="SyntheticBrew privacy policy: what information we collect, how it is used, analytics services, retention, security, and your data rights.">
  <article class="legal"><div class="container narrow">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1><p>Last modified: July 2026</p>
    <h2>1. Introduction</h2><p>SyntheticBrew (“we”, “us”, “our”) operates syntheticbrew.ai. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information.</p>
    <h2>2. Information we collect</h2><ul><li>Account data, including your email address and hashed password.</li><li>Payment data processed by Stripe; we do not store card numbers.</li><li>Usage metadata, such as login timestamps and feature usage counts.</li><li>Technical and analytics data, including IP address, device or browser information, page visits, link interactions, and referral information.</li></ul>
    <h2>3. How we use your data</h2><ul><li>Provide, secure, and maintain our services.</li><li>Process payments and manage subscriptions.</li><li>Send transactional messages such as password resets and billing notices.</li><li>Understand and improve product and website performance.</li><li>Prevent fraud, abuse, and unauthorized access.</li></ul>
    <h2>4. Service providers and sharing</h2><p>We use service providers only as needed to operate the service, including Stripe for payment processing, Resend for transactional email, Google Analytics 4 for website analytics, and Yandex Metrica for website analytics and interaction measurement. We do not sell personal data.</p>
    <h2>5. Analytics and local storage</h2><p>The website loads Google Analytics measurement ID <code>G-QM8W4T1H8S</code> and Yandex Metrica counter <code>109861753</code>. Yandex options currently include click mapping, session replay (Webvisor), link tracking, accurate bounce tracking, and ecommerce events through the site data layer. A pseudonymous account identifier may be associated with usage events. Browser settings, extensions, or provider opt-out tools may limit analytics collection.</p><p>The application uses browser localStorage for authentication tokens and interface preferences such as the theme choice.</p>
    <h2>6. Data retention</h2><ul><li>Active-account data is stored while the account exists.</li><li>Personal data associated with a deleted account is targeted for removal within 30 days, subject to backup and legal obligations.</li><li>Billing records are retained as required by law.</li><li>Aggregated or de-identified usage data may be retained longer.</li></ul>
    <h2>7. Your rights</h2><p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, export, restrict, object to, or delete personal data. Contact <a href="mailto:info@syntheticbrew.ai">info@syntheticbrew.ai</a> to submit a request.</p>
    <h2>8. Security</h2><p>We use measures including HTTPS/TLS, bcrypt password hashing, SHA-256 API token hashing, access controls, and security review. No system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2><p>We may update this policy. Changes will appear on this page with an updated “Last modified” date.</p>
    <h2>10. Contact</h2><p>For privacy questions, email <a href="mailto:info@syntheticbrew.ai">info@syntheticbrew.ai</a>. For product support, email <a href="mailto:support@syntheticbrew.ai">support@syntheticbrew.ai</a>.</p>
  </div></article>
</SiteLayout>
